@wurenhua The time and place of death of these 15 military policemen are as follows

Liu Guogeng, platoon leader of the Army's 63rd Group Army, died at around 4 a.m. on June 4, 1989, about 150 meters east of the Xidan intersection on West Chang'an Street.

Six soldiers of the Army's 38th Group Army, Wang Qifu, Li Qiang, Du Huaiqing, Li Dongguo, Wang Xiaobing, and Xu Rujun, died at around 1:10 a.m. on June 4, 1989, at the intersection of Cuiwei Road on the westward extension of West Chang'an Street.
